# Code Standards and Style Guidelines

## Overview

These guidelines establish fundamental code standards and style patterns that apply across all languages and frameworks in our codebase, with specific emphasis on TypeScript and React applications.

## Related Guidelines

- [Principles](mdc:principles.mdc) - Core development principles
- [Architecture](mdc:architecture.mdc) - System design patterns

## Directory Structure

### Project Organization

```sh
app/
├── api.ts                  # Root API configuration
├── components/            # Shared components
│   ├── ui/               # UI components
│   └── features/         # Feature components
├── lib/                  # Shared utilities
│   ├── client/          # Client-only code
│   ├── server/          # Server-only code
│   └── shared/          # Shared code
├── routes/               # File-based routes
│   ├── __root.tsx       # Root layout
│   ├── api/             # API routes
│   ├── _public/         # Public routes
│   ├── _auth/           # Auth routes
│   └── _app/            # Protected routes
├── types/               # Type definitions
└── tests/               # Test files
```

### General Principles

- Group files by feature or domain
- Separate concerns (UI, logic, types)
- Keep related files close together
- Use clear, descriptive directory names
- Maintain consistent depth

## Naming Conventions

### File Naming

1. Route Files:

   - `__root.tsx` - Root layout
   - `route.tsx` - Layout files
   - `index.tsx` - Page components
   - `[param].tsx` - Dynamic routes

2. API Routes:

   - `$.ts` - Catch-all handlers
   - `[feature].ts` - Feature-specific endpoints

3. Component Files:

   - Use PascalCase
   - Suffix with type: `.component.tsx`
   - Example: `UserProfile.component.tsx`

4. Server Functions:
   - Prefix with `$`
   - Use camelCase after prefix
   - Example: `$getUser`, `$updateProfile`

### Code Naming

1. Variables:

   ```typescript
   // ✅ Good
   const isUserAuthenticated = true;
   const handleProfileUpdate = () => {};

   // ❌ Bad
   const auth = true;
   const update = () => {};
   ```

2. Functions:

   ```typescript
   // ✅ Good
   function getUserProfile(id: string): Promise<User> {}
   const handleSubmit = async (data: FormData) => {};

   // ❌ Bad
   function getStuff(id) {}
   const submit = (data) => {};
   ```

## Code Organization

### File Structure

1. Order of Content:

   ```markdown
   1. File description/license
   2. Imports/dependencies
   3. Type definitions
   4. Constants
   5. Helper functions
   6. Main implementation
   7. Exports
   ```

### Import Organization

```typescript
// External dependencies
import { useState } from 'react';
import { createServerFn } from '@tanstack/start';

// Internal dependencies
import { UserProfile } from '~/components/features/user';
import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';

// Types
import type { User } from '~/lib/shared/types';
```

## Type Safety

### Type Definitions

1. Use `type` over `interface`:

   ```typescript
   // ✅ Good
   type UserData = {
     id: string;
     name: string;
   };

   // ❌ Bad - Don't use interface except in declare module
   interface UserData {
     id: string;
     name: string;
   }
   ```

2. Exception for `declare module`:

   ```typescript
   // ✅ Good - Interface in declare module
   declare module '@tanstack/react-router' {
     interface Register {
       router: ReturnType<typeof createRouter>;
     }
   }
   ```

## Error Handling

### Principles

1. Use Error Boundaries:

   ```typescript
   export function ErrorBoundary({ error }: { error: Error }) {
     return (
       <div role="alert">
         <p>Something went wrong:</p>
         <pre>{error.message}</pre>
       </div>
     );
   }
   ```

2. Handle Async Errors:

   ```typescript
   try {
     const data = await $fetchData();
     return json(data);
   } catch (error) {
     if (error instanceof ValidationError) {
       return json({ error: error.message }, { status: 400 });
     }
     throw error;
   }
   ```

## Documentation

### Comments

```typescript
// ✅ Good - Explains why, not what
// Retry three times to handle temporary network issues
function fetchWithRetry() { ... }

// ❌ Bad - States the obvious
// Function to fetch data
function fetchData() { ... }
```

### API Documentation

```typescript
/**
 * Brief description of purpose
 *
 * @param {type} name - Parameter description
 * @returns {type} Description of return value
 * @throws {type} Description of error cases
 */
```
